<article class="about-page">

  <div class="about-hero">
    <span class="about-tagline">The story</span>
    <h1>Named for<br><em>Imogen.</em></h1>
    <p class="about-intro">
      Immy's Cafe is a recipe site. No theme, no niche. Just the food we're
      actually making at home and thought was worth writing down.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="about-body">

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Who is Immy?</h2>
      <p>
        Immy is Imogen. She's the reason we started cooking more intentionally,
        and the reason the waffles exist. The site is named for her.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>What kind of recipes?</h2>
      <p>
        Whatever we're making. Some are weeknight dinners that have been in the rotation
        for a while. Some are things Imogen came up with. Some are things we found online
        and adjusted until they were right.
      </p>
      <p>
        If it made it to the table and we'd make it again, it goes on the site.
        That's the whole filter.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Why a website?</h2>
      <p>
        Partly to keep the recipes somewhere we can find them.
        Partly because writing them down forces you to actually know what you did.
        And partly because a few people asked.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="about-cta">
      <a href="/recipes/" class="btn-primary">
